# Testing and Validation Rule

Do not claim success without evidence.

- State exactly what you verified.
- Do not imply checks you did not run.
- Any meaningful behavior change should be validated.
- Prefer the narrowest relevant verification first.
- Follow existing repository testing style.
- Add or update tests when appropriate.
- Test behavior rather than implementation trivia where practical.
- If verification is incomplete, say so clearly.

Preferred order: narrow test -> type check -> lint -> build -> broader regression or golden check.
